Brown Bag Seafood on Randolph is my current favorite place to eat in Chicago.  I don't get to Chicago often, but I eat there when I do!  I've found their fish to be impeccably fresh and always well prepared.  The atmosphere is lovely, to my sensibilities.  It's a no-nonsense seafood shack, offering a menu that may seem limited, but which actually provides excellent fish in a range of dishes. It's definitely casual, maybe not "date night" material, but it feels authentic, welcoming, efficient,  and comfortable to me!  I've always found the place to be clean and inviting, with EXCELLENT staff,  great fish,  casual and comfortable surroundings, and wonderful views of the park...all in easy walking distance of the Loop.  Plus, I find it affordable, even by my Wisconsin standards.  My current favorite is the bowl with grains and veggies.  The grains are well flavored and nicely chewy; the veggies are fresh and well prepared...and a great complement to the always delicious fish.  I enjoy eating this.  It's tasty, but also feels very nourishing and satisfying.  I'm not sure how to explain what I mean, but, for me, there's a HUGE difference between grabbing some fast food when I just need some calories fast, or eating food that is delicious but not particularly healthy...and eating a meal that is delicious, nutritious, and totally satisfying on all fronts.  What more could one ask for?  It's my go-to when I'm in Chicago.

The food's good but I feel like it's a bit overpriced. Maybe they do that because it's a rich neighborhood.  Always order online. It's way faster and beats the lunch rush.
The quality of the food here is outstanding. The  chowder is creamy and delicious. I would like to see friendlier customer service at the counter. Today was an exception.

This spot is excellent for a work lunch... quick but good quality food! My favorite is the cornflake chicken on salad with lemon vinaigrette. The tots are also a great side item. Be sure to grab some 'boss sauce' from the sauce bar. Food is a bit overpriced though... $13 for chicken and a side of tots with tax is a bit steep for lunch.
Small portions, but good food.
Great quality for a great price! Fish is fresh and tasty and serving sizes are perfect. Will come back!

Lots of tasty options. I got the grilled fish tacos which were good. I had a side of classic slaw which, for my liking, had way too much celery in it. My husband got the white fish veggie box. He thought the veggies needed more seasoning. All that being said, I would definitely go back.

Try the lobster roll! I went on my last day in Chicago and regret I only found this place that day. I definitely would have loved to come back to try more off the menu. Staff was friendly, quick, and helpful to a first-timer.
It was okay, I think the fish is possibaly frozen and not fresh. The space is trendy and the grilled options with a salad are pretty good.
for 26 dollars i ordered a full lobster roll and its a tiny portion i get more full eating a tiny sushi than this

Great Sandwich. I had the blackened fish sandwich and the cheddar peppercorn tots. The combo of the fish, slaw and sauce on the sandwich was really good, and the tots were tasty as well. Will definitely be back to try more.

Way too messy.  Heavy on the slaw sauce.  And for the portion was overpriced.  Atmosphere was OK, bar top style seating.  Music was a bit loud, temperature was good on a hot day.  Would not eat here again. One of the  worst tacos we have had...And we love tacos.  Sad meal in Chicago..
Lobster roll and New England Clam Chowder were both delicious, though I'd say Da Lobsta lobster rolls are better
Good sandwiches 🥙
Best fast food ever! Awesome meal,cheap also. Original retro style:) 5 stars!!:)
Awesome. Fast, cheap and delicious
Nice view. Good food and great cocktail.
Fantastic food options. Healthy vs. Soul food options. Tasty choices. Easy and fast service.
Great little seafood place.  You write your own order and hand to the cashier.   The fish bites and salad was great! Right at $10.
